and get some §bWood§f!

Any type will complete the Quest.

You are probably familiar with this, hopefully.

How did you even get here without knowing the §bCrafting Table§f anyway?

Do you know what game you're playing at least?

One of the most useful resources in the game.

You'll need some §bFlint Tools§f to mine Stone.

Make sure to check out the §bTinkering quest section§f.
The Classic.
Take back the night!

Clay but with a white finish

With this you will be able to make the §bPorcelain Smeltery§f and later upgrade it to the §bSeared Bricks version§f.
Somewhere to store the useless stuff you find along the way.

One of the many ways to get resources early on.

Useful for when you can't get certain resources from another §bDimension§f.

When right clicking, you will start sieving in the §bSieve§k§f you right clicked and any other connected Sieves with the same §bMesh§f.

You'll need a decent pickaxe to mine this one.

You technically need only §b10§f obsidian blocks, but no one likes ugly Portals... that's why they're called ugly after all.

And you'll eventually need an §bEnchanting Table§f, so why not mine 14?

Your §bSmeltery§f will obviously need a steady supply of §bFuel§f, so that's why you might want to consider using a §bCrucible§f.

After providing it with a §bHeat Source§f underneath the Crucible will melt §bCobblestone§f into §bLava§f.

Agry dragon that won't get angrier the more you kill her.

Yes, its a her.

He too won't get angrier the more you kill it.

Later on you may need to make an impressive farm for him.
These hold many stacks of one item only and can be upgraded to hold even more storage.
Same deal as before, you can check the exact structure in the §f§bAstral Tome§f.

Spooky Forest.

To enter this dimension, dig a 2x2 (or 3x3) hole in the dirt, fill it with water, place flowers around the pond and throw a §bDiamond§f in it.

You may also get yourself a §bTraveler's Longbook§f to easily traverse the the forest and get more information on it.
First block to get into Botania, be sure to have a water source nearby.
This workbench is the first step into GalacticCraft. With it you can build many different rockets to land on many different planets, some more irrealistic than others
This is what happens to Iron Ingots when they go boom boom, preferably with a Creeper Throphy or some sort of mini TNT.

Using these §bPatterns§f inside of a §bPart Builder§f you will be able to create some §bParts§f using simple Materials.

You may want to utilize §bSharpening Kits§f in order to increase the §bMining Level §fof your Pickaxe.

Each one indicates which §bMining Level§f it has in the Tooltips.

The §bPorcelain Smeltery§f alllows you to start melting ores into their respective liquid form and use them to make §bSharpening Kits§f or §bTool Parts§f.

You will also be able to melt §bGrout§f and use it to make §bSeared Bricks§f.
Melt this to get seared bricks.

THE §bSmeltery§f.

§oNote: the bigger the laggier.

The §bStations§f to get started in Tinkers'.

-
The §bStencil Table§f allows you to create §bTool Patterns§f with §f§bBlank Patterns§f.

-
The §bPart Builder §fallows you to create §f§bTool Parts§f with §bTool Patterns§f.

-
The §bTool Station§f allows you to create §bTools §fwith §bTool Parts§f.

-
The §bPattern Chest§f and the §bParts Chest§b§f hold §bPatterns§f and §bParts§f respectively.
§bUpgrades§f for your Furnace.

§bCasts§f to use when dealing with Molten Materials.

Use them with the §bSmeltery§f to make §bTool Parts§f and combine these in the §bTool Station/Forge§f, depending on the Tool§f.
An improved version of the §bTool Station§f, used for crafting with higher tier Materials and new Tools.
The first tier Mesh you'll need in order to use the §bSieve§f.
Second tier Mesh.
Third tier Mesh.

The last tier Mesh.
 
You can also §benchant§f it to improve rates.
Using these §bPatterns§f inside of a §bPart Builder§f you will be able to create some §bParts§f using simple Materials.

The §bIndustrial Squeezer§f has many uses, from extracting Oil and other liquids from plants to combining Coke Dust.

Check the §bEngineer's Manual§f for a detailed explanation of how to make the multiblock structure.

The §bEngineer's Hammer§b§f is an essential tool to explore §bImmersive Engineering§f, from needing it for recipes to forming multiblock machines.

For the latter, check the §bEngineer's Manual§f to correctly know where to right click to form the machine.

The §bGarden Cloche§f§f is a simple machine that allows you to grow seeds faster than the traditional way.

After supplying one with a suitable §bS§f§boil§f, §b§fthe §bSeed§f that you want to grow, §bWater§f and §bPower§f, the §bGarden Cloche§f will start working.

§b§fThe §bMetal Press§f is one of the many multiblock machines that Immersive Engineering offers.

With this and some §bmolds§f you will be able to give metals different shapes and craft §bPlates§f or §bGears§f.

§b§fCheck the §bEngineer's Manual§f for a detailed explanation of how to make the multiblock structure.

A fidget spinner made out of 81 fidget spinners.

You'll need a lot of these spinny things.

With these you'll be able to make §bPatterns§f for different §bTool/Armor Parts§f inside the §bStencil Table§f.

Using the Patterns you made you will be able to create some Parts at the §bPart Builder§f out of rudimentary materials, like §bStone§f or §bFlint§f.

After making these Parts, you can combine them at a §bTool Station/Forge§f or at the §bArmor Station/Forge§f in the case of Armor parts.

The§b Luminous Crafting Table§f, the first tier in the Astral Sorcery world. 
§b§f
You may craft one by using a crafting table near a §bCollect Crystal§f, which you can find inside some of those marble temples scattered around the world.

It has to be placed somewhere in the world with sky access for it to fill up its §bStarlight meter§f. Placing it at high altitudes (max Y 120) will also get you more §bStarlight§f§k§f. The meter will obviously fill up only during the night

The §bLooking Glass§f allows you to look in the night sky for constellations, which will be useful later on.

Before using one, you will need to look for some§f §bConstellation Papers§b§f. which can be found in the world. These will give your Astral Tome a §bConstellations §fbookmark.

Once done, you will be able to point your §bLooking Glass §b§fat the night sky and look for some stars that stick out from the bunch.

After finding these, check the §bConstellations §fbookmark we mentioned before, look at the shape you're supposed to make and go back to your Looking Glass.

Here you want to hold shift and use the cursor to connect the stars in order to make the desired constellation.

The §bSpectral Relay§f allows you to gather additional Starlight, while requiring a §bstructur§f§be§f and a §bGlass Lens§f for it to work.

Check the Astral Tome, under the §bExploration§f section, for the shape of the required structure.

You obviously want it near your crafting table. You can make multiples aswell.

It also works during daytime!

Once placed above a §bMana Pool§f, you can place another §bSpark§f above something else that utilizes Mana, like the §bTerrestrial Agglomeration Plate§f!

This way, the above will be able to access the Mana reservoir and work properly.

You can also upgrade your Spark later on.

Place down the §bWood Table§f you crafted and right click it with the §bScribing Tools§f.

Once done, you will have your very own §bResearch Table§f and will be able to start your very own §b§f§bTheories§f, the second type of knowledge that Thaumcraft offers.

How does it work? It's basically a §bminigame§f!
Make sure to check the §bThaumonomicon§f for a more in-depth description.

You will be able to change the outcome of your §bTheories§f by placing the Research Table near other §bstations§f, like an Enchanting Table, a Bookshelf or a Crucible.

The slowest machine on the planet, ready to throw Neutronium at you while die of old age.

You'll need a lot of these bad boys.
Going vegetarian huh?
A lot of meat combined with some neutronium, tasty.
Right click on a block for a fun and destructive surprise.
A rainbow colored butter made out of 81 other different types of butter.
Combine the ultimate powers you've harvested so far into a colorful spike.
Made inside of an §bInscriber§f with different §bPresses§f.
A very powerlful white flower, capable of transforming adjacent Stone and Wood into §bLivingrock §fand §bLivingwood§f.

A valuable resource, used in many recipes.

Making a farm to quickly gather this rock may be a wise decision.

As the name implies, it keeps Mana in a Pool. Who would've thought?

There are many means of transporting Mana into a from the pool, like §bSparks§f!
A guide to get through Botania.

A portal that spits out certain items when you give it the right material.

§oNote: do not use it as a Trashcan§r.

Mana Steel in an Elven Portal, quite simple.

Useful for crafting many Botania items.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Agricrafting to the Moon and Back
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
§bCrop Sticks§f allow you to plant Seeds and other Flora on any valid Soil.

You can also §bCross-breed§f plants, either to get better ones or entirely new ones.

This is done by having an empty space with §b2 Crop Sticks§f between 2 other Plants.
The last chest you'll need.

not those crystals, Mark, not the white ones, stop it.

Gather some of those shiny colored rocks you find in the world and follow its advice.
Any type will complete the quest.
Better now than later

Shiny butter!

You can now consider yourself officially cool.
Your second step into Thermal's machines.
Your first step into Thermal's machines.

The size and layout is really up to you. Make sure to check out §b§1§2§2§3§4§5§5§6§7§8§9§a§b§c§d§b§f§k§l§o§r§2§3§9§b§9https://br.sidoh.org/§f

When building one, you can also use §bReactor Glass§f.

You can turn on your §bReactor§f with the §bReactor Controller§f or by sending a redstone signal through a §bReactor Redstone Port§f.

-
In order to make the Reactor work you will obviously need a Fuel, which in our case is §bYellorium§f. You can insert it using the §b§bReactor Access Port§f.

You can also use the §bReactor Access Port§f to extract the §bCyanite Waste§f you obtain from using §bYellorium§b§f.

Remember that every §bReactor Fuel Rod§f must have a §bReactor Control Rod§f on top of it.

The §bReactor Redstone Flux Power Tap§f will let you extract power from the internal buffer.

-
§b§fCoolants§f will obviously improve the efficiency of your Reactor, so leaving some spaces dedicated to §bCoolants§f in your Reactor is a good idea.

§bCoolants§f range from solid blocks (like Draconium Blocks or Iron Blocks) to liquids (like Resonant Ender or Gelid Cryotheum), which must be a source block.

The boss that Botania adds, drops Gaia Spirit on death.

Prepare well for this bossfight, both gearwise and arenawise.
The §bGoggle of Revealing§f are a useful piece of equipment, which allows the user to, for example, monitor the amount of §bEssentia§f in a §bCrucible §for in jars.
This small and easy to get item allows you to extract §bEssentia§f from a §bCrucible§f and turn it into its original crystal form.

A magical furnace that turns objects into §bEssentia§f, a bit like the §bCrucible§f, using fuel. Any will do, but the fastest fuel for it is §bAlumentum§f.

By itself, it is pretty much useless, so let's give it a friend, the §bArcane Alembic§f!
Using this, you will be able to start storiing the §bEssentia§f you're getting.

To do so, you'll either want to use some §btubes§f or go the lazy way: the §bFilling Essentia Transfuser§b§f, which will make the §bEssentia§f go inside an available §bjar§f.

Talking about jars, it's what you'll need to store this §bEssentia§f! Be sure to craft multiple §bWarded Jars§f.

Also, don't forget to label your jars with some §bBlank Labels§f!
Just like the §bEssentia Smeltery§b§f, but instead of 80% efficiency, it has §b90%§§.
Now that you have a storage for your §bEssentia§f, you'll be able to fill some §bPhials§f with the §bArcane Alembic§f or with a §bWarded Jar§f!§f

In order to even make a portal to the §bErebus§f, you will need to craft the §bStaff of Gaea§f, which requires the §bGaean Gem§f. 
To get one, you will be required to craft an §bOffering Altar§f and right click it with a §bDiamond§f, an §bEmerald§f, and a piece of §bObsidian§f.

Now, to enter this realm of bugs and insects, make a §bPortal frame out of bricks§f, the size doesn't matter.

After that, fill it in with §bLeaves§f of any type, place the §bGaean Keystone§f next to it and right click it with the §bStaff of Gaea§f.

Some sort of flight device is recommended to explore this hellhole.

Good luck.

Transforms any block that gets right clicked with this Magical Rod into a §bMob§f that drops the block it was before upon Death.

Great way to farm Resources, probably the best one.

The §bInfusion Altar§f, as the name says, is a very special altar that uses §bEssentia§f and some items for crafting even rarer items.

To build the correct §b§bstructure§f, check the §bThaumonomicon§f, right click the §bRunic Matrix§f with §bSalis Mundus§f and you'll be good to go!

The recipes that utilize the §d§d§bInfusion Altar§f, also require some §bEssentia§f, so make sure to have nearby some jars with the correct one!

Another important feature is the use of §bPedestals§f, which vary in number from recipe to recipe. You will need to place these in the correct position for the recipe to work, the distance shouldn't matter.

Once that everything is ready, you'll have to right click the §bRunic Matrix§f with the §bCaster's Gauntlet§f, which will animate the Matrix the first time. 
To start the crafting process, after having set up each required item on the pedestals and having §b§fthe required Essentia, you will just need to right click the Matrix with the Gauntlet.

For more information on §bstability§f and other very useful information on the §bInfusion Altar§b§f, check the §bThaumonomicon§f.

§o(Make sure to have the required tasks and chapters unlocked in the Thaumonomicon before)§r

Looks like you haven't been that careful with that §bFlux§f build-up, and a §b§bFlux Rift§k§f appeared!

While very mesmerizing, it will destroy blocks in its way, while consuming some of the §bFlux§f in the chunk, so its not that bad, is it?

To remove it, you'll need a §bCausality Collapser§f, which is basically a grenade that deletes a §bFlux Rift§f, leaving behind only §bVoid Seeds§f.
Using the §bVoid Seeds§b§f you gathered, you will now be able to create §bVoid Metal§f!

Another way of closing §bFlux Rifts§f is using a §bVoid Siphon§f, which will harvest the power of the Rift and produce some §bVoid Seeds§f.

You can pause it with a redstone signal.

An upgrade§b§fd §bCrucible§f, where you can select the recipe you want to make and that draws §bEssentia §ffrom nearby sources.

To make one, place §b2 Alchemical Construct § above a standard§b Crucible§f and right click with a piece of §bSalis Mundus§f.

Note that it will still require a source of heat under it.

Another item that you may craft near a §b§f§o§f§b§d§c§c§b§a§9§8§7§6§6§b§0§1§2§3§4§4§3§bCollector Crystal§f.

This wand will let you §bcomplete recipes§f (by right clicking the crafting table after the ingredients have been inserted) and find §bCrystal Ores§f during the night, thanks to some glowing light effects coming from the ground.

Remember those §f§bCrystal Ores§f from before? Yup, we'll need them now. Make sure to pick the lowest purity §bRock Crystal§f!

Using the Luminous Crafting Table, you'll be able to craft the §bLightwell§f, basically a tank for Starlight.

With it you can produce §bStarlight§f using different Astral Sorcery items (Aquamarine, Resonating Gems, Rock Crystals and Celestial Crystals) and hold up to 2 buckets.

Now that you can make some buckets of §bStarlight§f, why not put them to use?

With a §bFosic Resonator§f you will be able to locate areas of your world with §bhigher Starlight concentration§f. Just hold it in your hand and look for areas with a blue cloud of smoke.

It's time to upgrade your Luminous Crafting Table to a §bStarlight Crafting Altar§f!

After right clicking with your §bResonating Wand§f, your Luminous Crafting Table will be converted into a Starlight Crafting Altar, which needs a §bspecific structure§f for it to be used.

To see the shape of this structure check the Astral Tome, under the §bExploration§f section.

The §bLinking Tool§f, as the name says, is used to link many different things together.

A simple example is linking together a §bRock Crystal§f and any §bAltar§f in order to have usable §bStarlight§f during the daytime.
A very useful machine to get into Actually Additions.

Before being able to craft a §bCobblestone Generator§f, you will need other resources, which require quite a bit of cobblestone themselves.

This is why you may need to make an §bold fashion Generator§f!

§bLava§f, §bWater§f, a §bTransfer Node §fand a §bMining Upgrade§b§f.

In order to function, you simply need to place a §bLava Source§f, a §bCobblestone Block§f next to the Lava and a §bWater Source§b§f next to the Cobble.

§fOnce you've replicated this exact setup, you can place the §bTransfer Node§f with the §bMining Upgrade§f on the §bCobblestone§f and it'll start mining.
The §bCrook§f is a useful tool to quickly gather more §bFruits§f and get §bSilk Worms§b§f from §bTree Leaves§f.

The §bPumpjack§f, after being provided with some power, will allow you to extract §bOil§f from the depths of your world.

§oNote: this does not refer to the Oil you can find in ponds underground or on the surface§r.

It's a far quicker and cleaner way of gathering §bOil§f than using buckets and tanks, that's for sure.

Check the §bEngineer's Manual§f for a detailed explanation of how to make the multiblock structure.

Using the §bDistillation Tower§f you will be able to process the §bOil§f you extracted in many biproducts, some of which are §bBitumen§f and §bLubricant§f.

Check the §bEngineer's Manual§f for a detailed explanation of how to make the multiblock structure.

Once again, same deal as before, you can see the correct structure in the §bAstral Tome§f, but this time you will also need some §bSpectral Relays§f on the ground, since the table cant hold all the items by itself.

It will also require an §bAttuned Crystal§f to the correct Constellation required in the recipe you're following.
Infinite Mana!
Better now than later
Better now than later

This colorful guy gives you a lot more channels to work with to expand your ME System.

You'll need some for sure if you plan on autocrafting.
And trust me, you better plan to.

It's wireless.
It's a crafting terminal.

Needs more explaining?
You'll need one, there are no fluid cows this time.

A complete §bguide§f for Astral Sorcery.

Other than doing that, it also has some practical uses, like holding your research on constellations.

It also covers some items and mechanics that aren't covered by quests, make sure to check them out!

To quickly navigate it, you can double click on each Chapter.
Just like the §bTool Forge§f, it's an improved version of the §bArmor Station§f, used for crafting with higher tier Materials.
The §bArmor Station§f allows you to create §bArmor Pieces §fwith §bArmor Parts§f.
Use them with the §bSmeltery§f to make §bArmor Parts§f and combine these in the §bArmor Forge§f.

Welcome to Logistics Pipes!

The first step is aquiring a §bLogistics Power Junction§f, which will provide Power and make work any attached §bPipes§f.

Obviously you will need some §bPower§f for this Machine to work.

§bUnbreakable§f Tools!

Apply these with the Tool Forge.

The best hunter, the one that sits while his contraptions do all the work.

This machine, after giving it a §bRedstone Signal§f will start damaging any entity in its path.

You can also upgrade its §bLooting§f, §bSharpness§f and §bBeheading§f, aswell as others.

A way to improve your Mob Farm, §bCursed Earth§f.

§bRight click§f any §bDirt§f block with a §bDrop of Evil§f to turn it into Cursed Earth.

§4WARNING§f: the amount of mobs it spawns can very well get you killed if you don't take any precautions.

Iron Chests, Gold Chests and Diamond Chests.

Either §bupgrade§f the Vanilla Chest with Upgrades or directly §bcraft§f the Chests.

§bAnimation§f and §bDuplication§f is key.

Might aswell build a house with them. Maybe a mansion.
A door to everything Mekanism

The manual for everything Immersive Engineering.

This book will help you a lot, be sure to have one around.
A 3x3x3 "Furnace" that takes §bCoal§f and turns it into §bCoal Coke§f, all while making some §bCreosote Oil§f.

Yet another 3x3x3 "Furnace". 

Takes Iron and Fuel to convert it into §bSteel§f.

§oNote: since you'll need Blaze Powder to craft the Bricks, try looking into sifting some Dust§f.

An improved §bBlast Furnace§f.

To build it, you will need to arrange the §bReinforced Blast Bricks§f in a 3x3x3, with a hopper on top of it in the middle.

You can add up to 2 §bBlast Furnace Preheaters§f to the Furnace to speed it up.
The §bEngineer's Workbench§f will allow you to make different crafting compononents required in different recipes and some tools for machines like the §f§bMetal Press§f.

Another "Furnace", but this time 2x2x2! 

The §bAlloy Kiln§f, as the name implies, takes different materials and alloys them together.
Useful resource in the Engineer's world, made with creosote oil and some wood.

Quite an interesting powder, made with some of those §bVis Crystals§f found around the world.

This item is a fundamental to start exploring Thaumcraft and will allow you to transform ordinary items into magical and powerful devices.

Some flowers you can use to generate mana quickly, these aren't all the options out there at all. 

Be creative.

A complete §bguide§f that outlines everything that Thaumcraft offers!

Make sure to follow the §bprogression§f it outlines! You cannot progress through the mod without completing each §btask/chapter§f that the book illustrates.

§bSalis Mundus§f, a §bCrafting Table§f and the right mouse button, what a combination!

The §bArcane Crafting Table§f is a very important piece in making many of the Thaumcraft items.

§b§k§fSome recipes, like the §bThaumometer§f, will require you to have all the crystals, so make sure you have a good amount!

When crafting, you'll notice that each Thaumcraft recipe will have a §bVis requirement§f, which refers to the amount of §bVis§f that each chunk has. You can check the amount of §bVis§f with a §bThaumometer§f, by looking in the top left.

Remember that the amount of §bVis§f in a chunk can be lowered by the amount of §bFlux §fthat is also present there. §b
Flux§f is a dangerous entity, so make sure you have your §b§fThaumcraft dedicated area away from your base. §
Check the §bCrucible §fquest for more information on §§how §f§bFlux§f is generated.

To learn about §bEssentia§f, progress to the §bCrucible§f quest.

After crafting this magical device, §b§fyou will be able to right click on many things, particularly on those that have some §bshiny particles on them§f. 

These will give you points towards the first type of research that Thaumcraft has, §bObservation§f.

To quickly gain knowledge, you can put items in a chest and right click it with your §bThaumometer§f.

§bSalis Mundus§f, §bCauldron§f, you know the drill.

The §bCrucible§f will allow you to craft many items, but this time with a twist.

You will be required to use §bEssentia§f, which every item in the game has§b§f, and usually another item.

Every recipe will ask for a set of §bEssentia§f, which some items may have. If they do, you can throw in the §bCrucible§f that particular item, and the §b§fset of §bEssentia§f it has will be used for the recipe. Otherwise, you can simply throw in items with the §bEssentia§f that you need.

You may also use §bVis Crystals§b§f as a source of §bEssentia§f.

Flux§f is generated when releasing §bEssentia§f into the world without filtering it (for example when it dissolves from a §bCrucible§f after some time), so make sure you don't wait too long for creating an item.

Remember that you will need a heat source under the §bCrucible§f for it to work, like some §bLava§f!

The §bBag Opener§f, as the name says, opens §bLootbags§b§f for you, with some wait time in between each Bag. 

It has an internal buffer, so it is able to store some items, but extracting them is the best solution when it is connected to a working Mob Farm.

Before that we need a §bLogistics Program Compiler§f, which needs to be connected to the §bLogistics Power Junction§f with a §bBasic Logistics Pipe§f.

The §bLogistics Programmer§f is a key ingredient in the crafting of better and more complex Pipes.

After unlocking any Tier with the §bLogistics Disk§f, on the right of the §bLogistics Program Compiler§f's interface some Pipes will appear, which can be compiled and then §bflashed§f into the §bLogistics Programmer§f.

The process of §bcompiling§f simply unlocks that particular Pipe configuration, so that you can §bflash§f it at any point in time.

Once done, you will be able to use that particular configuration inside of the §bLogistics Programmer §fto craft that particular Pipe.

Its tooltip will also tell you which configuration it currently holds.

In order to use the §bLogistics Program Compiler§f, we first need a §bLogistics Disk§f, which will remember every Tier of Pipes we unlocked and needs to be placed inside of the Compiler.

Once inside the §bLogistics Program Compiler§f, we can start unlocking different Tiers, starting with the §bBasic§f one, which will allow you to later program that blue thing we talked about before.

The are many different kinds of §bPipes§f, but we'll focus on the basics.

The first Pipes you'll want to make are §bUnrouted Transport Pipes§f, which are simply dumb pipes that follow a random direction when at an intersection.

To avoid this problem, we have to put §bBasic Logistics Pipes§f at intersections.

§bBasic Logistics Pipes§f can also be configured with, for example, a §bCrecent Hammer§f, which will allow you to, among other things, set the Inventory to which it is connected as a §bDefault Destination§f.

This means that any item that is inserted will first try going to this Inventory.

Remember that Pipes always indicate if something is wrong, you just need to look out for Red Stripes on them, and if items are unable to go inside of an Inventory while no other Inventory is availble, the Pipe will simply spit them out.

You can find it in the Basic Tier.
